public class SoftButton
extends Button
implements com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.SourcesMouseEvents, com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.SourcesMouseWheelEvents

This is a button widget implemented entirely without the native button widget. This avoids Z-index overlay problems, and provides enhanced functionality.

Base CSS class: gwittir-SoftButton

Extended CSS Classes:

  • disabled
  • focussed
  • pressed
  • hover

Example styling: 

 .gwittir-SoftButton.disabled {
    border-style: inset;
    border-width: 2px;
    color: gray;
    background-color: white;
 }

This is implemented with a base CSS style of table, so table based CSS attributes like vertical-align may be applied.

Author:
Robert "kebernet" Cooper
